abstract: Bomb-laden car explodes at gate of Somali presidential palace in Mogadishu, killing four and wounding another dozen; militant Islamist group Shabab claims responsibility.
lead_paragraph: The Shabab, a militant Islamist group affiliated with Al Qaeda, said the attack had targeted senior Somali and foreign officials.

headline.main: Deadly Car Bombing at Somalia’s Presidential Palace Is Claimed by Shabab
headline.print_headline: Deadly Car Bombing at Somalia’s Presidential Palace Is Claimed by Shabab
